propertyDefinition.name: Cost Per Volume
propertyDefinition.description: Dollars

propertyDefinition.name: Total Cost of Volume
propertyDefinition.description: Expresses the cost property in terms of volume unit, and multiplies it by the element's volume

propertyDefinition.name: Total Cost of Volume (USD)
propertyDefinition.description:
Converts the cost per volume expression into a String.
Adds another string ("USD") to the result.
The expression must be evaluated using each element's specific Conditional Volume property.

propertyDefinition.name: Total Cost of Volume ($)
propertyDefinition.description:
Converts the cost per volume expression into a String.
Adds another string ("$") to the result.
The expression must be evaluated using each element's specific Conditional Volume property.

propertyDefinition.name: Beam Overhang
propertyDefinition.description: Amount of extra beam length required as overhang. Overhang is either 10 cm (for beams less than 4.8m) or 12 cm (for beams longer than 4.8m)

propertyDefinition.name: Prefab beam length increment
propertyDefinition.description: Beams are available for purchase in this length increment (mm)

propertyDefinition.name: Maximum beam span
propertyDefinition.description: Returns the beam span when the beam is modeled exactly between the structures to be bridged.

propertyDefinition.name: Beam length to be purchased
propertyDefinition.description: Estimates the beam length to be ordered, including overhang, and taking into consideration the length increment available for purchase (30 cm increments)

propertyDefinition.name: Product location
propertyDefinition.description: For furnishing-type objects: Creates a string that identifies their location in the building (Project, Building, Story and Room information)

propertyDefinition.name: Context ID

propertyDefinition.name: Dynamic ID by Classification

propertyDefinition.name: Hotlinked Door Context ID

propertyDefinition.name: Stair Subelements - Numerical IDs
propertyDefinition.description: Lists elements using the second (numerical) part of their Element ID

propertyDefinition.name: R / G result
propertyDefinition.description: Calculates the R / G value for Stair elements

propertyDefinition.name: R / G result formula
propertyDefinition.description: Produces a string containing R / G value of a Stair-Ramp element, in the format "R / G = number"

propertyDefinition.name: R + G result
propertyDefinition.description: Calculates the R + G value for Stair elements

propertyDefinition.name: Name
propertyDefinition.description: Name of the material.

propertyDefinition.name: Category
propertyDefinition.description: Definition of the category (group or type) of material, in more general terms than given by attribute Name.

propertyDefinition.name: Description
propertyDefinition.description: Definition of the material in more descriptive terms than given by attributes Name or Category.

propertyDefinition.name: Relates To
propertyDefinition.description: Reference to a material relationship indicating that this material composite has parts (or constituents).

propertyDefinition.name: Is related with
propertyDefinition.description: Reference to a material relationship indicating that this material is a part (or constituent) in a material composite.

propertyDefinition.name: Porosity
propertyDefinition.description:
The void fraction of the total volume occupied by material (Vbr - Vnet)/Vbr.
Units: A dimensionless measure to express ratio values ranging from 0.0 to 1.0.

propertyDefinition.name: Mass Density
propertyDefinition.description: Material mass density. Usually measured in kg/m3.

propertyDefinition.name: Compressive Strength
propertyDefinition.description:
The compressive strength of the concrete. 
Units: Usually measured in Pascals (Pa, N/m2).

propertyDefinition.name: Max Aggregate Size
propertyDefinition.description: The maximum aggregate size of the concrete

propertyDefinition.name: Admixtures Description
propertyDefinition.description: Description of the admixtures added to the concrete mix.

propertyDefinition.name: Workability
propertyDefinition.description: Description of the workability of the fresh concrete defined according to local standards.

propertyDefinition.name: Water Impermeability
propertyDefinition.description: Description of the water impermeability denoting the water repelling properties.

propertyDefinition.name: Protective Pore Ratio
propertyDefinition.description:
The protective pore ratio indicating the frost-resistance of the concrete.
Units: A dimensionless measure to express ratio values ranging from 0.0 to 1.0.

propertyDefinition.name: Yield Stress
propertyDefinition.description:
A measure of the yield stress (or characteristic 0.2 percent proof stress) of the material. 
Usually measured in Pascals (Pa, N/m2).

propertyDefinition.name: Ultimate Stress
propertyDefinition.description:
A measure of the ultimate stress of the material.
Usually measured in Pascals (Pa, N/m2).

propertyDefinition.name: Ultimate Strain
propertyDefinition.description:
A measure of the (engineering) strain at the state of ultimate stress of the material.
Units: A ratio measure that is greater than zero. Input given in percent is to be divided by 100%. For example, 25% becomes 0.25.

propertyDefinition.name: Hardening Module
propertyDefinition.description:
A measure of the hardening module of the material (slope of stress versus strain curve after yield range).
Units: Usually measured in N/m2.

propertyDefinition.name: Proportional Stress
propertyDefinition.description:
A measure of the proportional stress of the material. It describes the stress before the first plastic deformation occurs and is commonly measured at a deformation of 0.01%. 
Units: Usually measured in Pascals (Pa, N/m2).

propertyDefinition.name: Plastic Strain
propertyDefinition.description:
A measure of the permanent displacement, as in slip or twinning, which remains after the stress has been removed. Currently applied to a strain of 0.2% proportional stress of the material.
Units: A ratio measure that is greater than zero.

propertyDefinition.name: Relaxations
propertyDefinition.description:
Measures of decrease in stress over long time intervals resulting from plastic flow. Different relaxation values for different initial stress levels for a material may be given. It describes the time dependent relative relaxation value for a given initial stress level at constant strain. 
Units: A dimensionless measure to express ratio values ranging from 0.0 to 1.0.

propertyDefinition.name: Species
propertyDefinition.description: Wood species of a solid wood or laminated wood product.

propertyDefinition.name: Strength Grade
propertyDefinition.description: Grade with respect to mechanical strength and stiffness.

propertyDefinition.name: Appearance Grade
propertyDefinition.description: Grade with respect to visual quality.

propertyDefinition.name: Layup
propertyDefinition.description: Configuration of the lamination.

propertyDefinition.name: Layers
propertyDefinition.description: Number of layers.

propertyDefinition.name: Plies
propertyDefinition.description: Number of plies.

propertyDefinition.name: Moisture Content
propertyDefinition.description:
Total weight of moisture relative to oven-dried weight of the wood.
Units: Greater than zero. Input given in percent is to be divided by 100%. For example, 25% becomes 0.25.

propertyDefinition.name: Dimensional Change Coefficient
propertyDefinition.description:
Weighted dimensional change coefficient, relative to 1% change in moisture content.
Units: Greater than zero. Input given in percent is to be divided by 100%. For example, 25% becomes 0.25.

propertyDefinition.name: Thickness Swelling
propertyDefinition.description:
Swelling ratio relative to board depth.
Units:Greater than zero. Input given in percent is to be divided by 100%. For example, 25% becomes 0.25.

propertyDefinition.name: Specific Heat Capacity
propertyDefinition.description:
Specific heat of the products of combustion: heat energy absorbed per temperature unit.
Usually measured in J / kg Kelvin.

propertyDefinition.name: N2O Content
propertyDefinition.description: Nitrous oxide (N2O) content of the products of combustion. This is measured in weight of N2O per unit weight and is therefore unitless.

propertyDefinition.name: CO Content
propertyDefinition.description: Carbon monoxide (CO) content of the products of combustion. This is measured in weight of CO per unit weight and is therefore unitless.

propertyDefinition.name: CO2 Content
propertyDefinition.description: Carbon dioxide (CO2) content of the products of combustion. This is measured in weight of CO2 per unit weight and is therefore unitless.

propertyDefinition.name: Specific Heat Capacity
propertyDefinition.description: Defines the specific heat of the material: heat energy absorbed per temperature unit. Usually measured in J / kg Kelvin.

propertyDefinition.name: Boiling Point
propertyDefinition.description: The boiling point of the material (fluid). Usually measured in degrees Kelvin (K).

propertyDefinition.name: Freezing Point
propertyDefinition.description: The freezing point of the material (fluid). Usually measured in degrees Kelvin (K).

propertyDefinition.name: Thermal Conductivity
propertyDefinition.description: The rate at which thermal energy is transmitted through the material. Usually measured in Watt / m Kelvin.

propertyDefinition.name: Upper Vapor Resistance Factor
propertyDefinition.description:
The vapor permeability relationship of air/material (typically value > 1), measured in high relative humidity (typically in 95/50 % RH).
Units: ratio measure that is greater than zero.

propertyDefinition.name: Lower Vapor Resistance Factor
propertyDefinition.description:
The vapor permeability relationship of air/material (typically value > 1), measured in low relative humidity (typically in 0/50 % RH).
Units: ratio measure that is greater than zero.

propertyDefinition.name: Isothermal Moisture Capacity
propertyDefinition.description:
Based on water vapor density.
Usually measured in m3/kg.

propertyDefinition.name: Vapor Permeability
propertyDefinition.description:
The rate of water vapor transmission per unit area per unit of vapor pressure differential under test conditions.
Usually measured in kg / s m Pascal.

propertyDefinition.name: Moisture Diffusivity
propertyDefinition.description:
Moisture diffusivity is a transport property that is frequently used in the hygrothermal analysis of building envelope components.
Units: Usually measured in m3/s.

propertyDefinition.name: Dynamic Viscosity
propertyDefinition.description:
A measure of the viscous resistance of the material.
Usually measured in Pascal second (Pa s).

propertyDefinition.name: Young Modulus
propertyDefinition.description:
A measure of the Young's modulus of elasticity of the material.
Usually measured in N/m2.

propertyDefinition.name: Shear Modulus
propertyDefinition.description:
A measure of the shear modulus of elasticity of the material.
Usually measured in N/m2.

propertyDefinition.name: Poisson Ratio
propertyDefinition.description:
A measure of the lateral deformations in the elastic range.
A ratio measure that is greater than zero.

propertyDefinition.name: Thermal Expansion Coefficient
propertyDefinition.description:
A measure of the expansion coefficient for warming up the material about one Kelvin.
 It is usually measured in 1/K. A positive elongation per (positive) rise of temperature is expressed by a positive value.

propertyDefinition.name: Visible Transmittance
propertyDefinition.description:
Transmittance at normal incidence (visible). Defines the fraction of the visible spectrum of solar radiation that passes through per unit area, perpendicular to the surface.
Units: A ratio measure that is greater than zero.

propertyDefinition.name: Solar Transmittance
propertyDefinition.description:
Transmittance at normal incidence (solar). Defines the fraction of solar radiation that passes through per unit area, perpendicular to the surface.
Units: A ratio measure that is greater than zero.

propertyDefinition.name: Thermal Transmittance
propertyDefinition.description:
Thermal IR transmittance at normal incidence. Defines the fraction of thermal energy that passes through per unit area, perpendicular to the surface.
Units: A ratio measure that is greater than zero.

propertyDefinition.name: Thermal Ir Emissivity Back
propertyDefinition.description:
Thermal IR emissivity: back side. Defines the fraction of thermal energy emitted per unit area to "blackbody" at the same temperature, through the "back" side of the material.
Units: A ratio measure that is greater than zero.

propertyDefinition.name: Thermal Ir Emissivity Front
propertyDefinition.description:
Thermal IR emissivity: front side. Defines the fraction of thermal energy emitted per unit area to "blackbody" at the same temperature, through the "front" side of the material.
Units: A ratio measure that is greater than zero.

propertyDefinition.name: Visible Reflectance Back
propertyDefinition.description:
Reflectance at normal incidence (visible): back side. Defines the fraction of the solar ray in the visible spectrum that is reflected and not transmitted when the ray passes from one medium into another, at the "back" side of the other material, perpendicular to the surface. Dependent on material and surface characteristics.
Units: A ratio measure that is greater than zero.

propertyDefinition.name: Visible Reflectance Front
propertyDefinition.description:
Reflectance at normal incidence (visible): front side. Defines the fraction of the solar ray in the visible spectrum that is reflected and not transmitted when the ray passes from one medium into another, at the "front" side of the other material, perpendicular to the surface. Dependent on material and surface characteristics.
Units: A ratio measure that is greater than zero.

propertyDefinition.name: Solar Reflectance Back
propertyDefinition.description:
Reflectance at normal incidence (solar): back side. Defines the fraction of the solar ray that is reflected and not transmitted when the ray passes from one medium into another, at the "back" side of the other material, perpendicular to the surface. Dependent on material and surface characteristics.
Units: A ratio measure that is greater than zero.

propertyDefinition.name: Solar Reflectance Front
propertyDefinition.description:
Reflectance at normal incidence (solar): front side. Defines the fraction of the solar ray that is reflected and not transmitted when the ray passes from one medium into another, at the "front" side of the other material, perpendicular to the surface. Dependent on material and surface characteristics.
Units: A ratio measure that is greater than zero.

propertyDefinition.name: Strength Grade
propertyDefinition.description: The quality grade of the material. Use a commonly known naming of grades of specific structural material. For Example: C25/30, S 235, etc...
